  "prompt": "What do the lyrics mean in \"Vienna\" by Billy Joel?",
  "response": "The song \"Vienna\" is essentially a thoughtful message about not rushing through life or being too hard on yourself. Billy Joel seems to be advising a young person (possibly representing youth in general) to slow down, take their time, and understand that life isn't a race. \n\nThe lyrics suggest that while young people often feel pressure to accomplish everything quickly, there's value in patience and allowing yourself to develop at your own pace. \"Vienna\" is metaphorical - representing a place of rest, reflection, and self-acceptance.\n\nThe core message encourages listeners not to be too critical of themselves, reminding them that they have time to grow, learn, and achieve their goals. It's about understanding that personal development is a journey, and you don't need to have everything figured out immediately.\n\nThe song implies that society often pushes young people to achieve rapidly, but true wisdom comes from taking time to understand yourself and not burning out in the process. It's a compassionate perspective on personal growth and self-worth.",
